  "prompt": "How does it feel not to love someone knowing that they truly love you?",
  "response": "Navigating a situation where someone loves you but you don't share the same feelings can be challenging and emotionally complex. You might experience a mix of emotions, such as empathy, guilt, or confusion. It can be difficult to see someone you care about feeling hurt or disappointed. At the same time, it's important to remain true to your own feelings and to recognize that you can't force love.\n\nHonesty and clear communication can be vital in these situations. Compassionately expressing your feelings and setting boundaries can help both parties move forward in a healthy way. It's important to approach the situation with kindness and understanding, both for the other person and for yourself.",
